https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/rockcms/2026-05/260501-rob-sand-mb-1308-24a109.jpg" type="image/jpeg" medium="image" height="1667" width="2500"><media:credit>Charlie Neibergall</media:credit><media:text type="plain">Election 2026 Iowa Governor</media:text><media:description type="plain">Rep. Zach Nunn, R-Iowa, in Washington in 2024.</media:description></media:content><media:thumbnail url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/rockcms/2026-05/260501-zach-nunn-mb-1303-ce4086.jpg" height="1667" width="2500"></media:thumbnail><pubDate>Tue, 05 May 2026 09:00:40 GMT</pubDate><title>Republicans fret over Iowa as tough midterm races develop</title><updateDate>Tue, 05 May 2026 12:48:34 GMT</updateDate></item><item><dc:creator>Kaitlin Sullivan</dc:creator><dateTimeWritten>Tue, 05 May 2026 15:00:00 GMT</dateTimeWritten><description>A single psychedelic trip may cause physical changes in the brain that could explain why some people report psychological benefits from the experience, a small study suggests.</description><expires>2112-01-01T00:00:00.000+0000</expires><guid>https://www.nbcnews.com/health/health-news/science-gets-closer-understanding-psychedelic-trip-changes-brain-rcna343537</guid><link>https://www.nbcnews.com/health/health-news/science-gets-closer-understanding-psychedelic-trip-changes-brain-rcna343537</link><media:content url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/rockcms/2023-03/230316-psilocybin-mushrooms-jm-1208-1d002b.jpg" type="image/jpeg" medium="image" height="1667" width="2500"><media:credit>The Washington Post</media:credit><media:text type="plain">Psilocybin mushrooms in Washington, D.C., on Feb. 5, 2020.</media:text><media:description type="plain">The study focused on psilocybin, the psychedelic compound found in so-called magic mushrooms.</media:description></media:content><media:thumbnail url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/rockcms/2023-03/230316-psilocybin-mushrooms-jm-1208-1d002b.jpg" height="1667" width="2500"></media:thumbnail><pubDate>Tue, 05 May 2026 15:00:00 GMT</pubDate><title>Science gets closer to understanding how a psychedelic trip changes the brain</title><updateDate>Tue, 05 May 2026 15:00:00 GMT</updateDate></item><item><dateTimeWritten>Tue, 05 May 2026 13:18:53 GMT</dateTimeWritten><description>Blake Lively attended the Met Gala on Monday after reaching a settlement with former co-star and director Justin Baldoni, bringing an abrupt end to their year-long legal battle. Lively sued Baldoni and his production company for waging what she called a smear campaign against her after she accused him of sexual harassment on the set of their 2024 film “It Ends With Us,” which Baldoni consistently denied. NBC’s Laura Jarrett reports for TODAY.</description><expires>2056-05-05T12:31:58.000+0000</expires><guid isPermaLink="false">tdy_news_8a_jarrett_lively_baldoni_settlement_260505</guid><link>https://www.today.com/video/it-ends-with-a-deal-justin-baldoni-and-blake-lively-settle-lawsuit-262752837843</link><media:content url="https://prodamdnewsencoding.akamaized.net/NBC_News_Digital/tdy_news_8a_jarrett_lively_baldoni_settlement_260505/1/abs/index.m3u8" medium="video"><media:credit></media:credit><media:title>Blake Lively and Justin Baldoni Settle ‘It Ends With Us’ Legal Battle</media:title><media:player url="https://www.today.com/video/it-ends-with-a-deal-justin-baldoni-and-blake-lively-settle-lawsuit-262752837843"></media:player><media:thumbnail url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/mpx/2704722219/2026_05/1777984306135_tdy_news_8a_jarrett_lively_baldoni_settlement_260505_S3_1920x1080-te6gza.jpg"></media:thumbnail><media:description type="plain">Blake Lively attended the Met Gala on Monday after reaching a settlement with former co-star and director Justin Baldoni, bringing an abrupt end to their year-long legal battle. Lively sued Baldoni and his production company for waging what she called a smear campaign against her after she accused him of sexual harassment on the set of their 2024 film “It Ends With Us,” which Baldoni consistently denied. NBC’s Laura Jarrett reports for TODAY.</media:description><media:subTitle type="text/srt" lang="en-US" url="https://prodamdnewsencoding.akamaized.net/NBC_News_Digital/nbcnews/captions/2026/05/1777984306135_tdy_news_8a_jarrett_lively_baldoni_settlement_260505.srt"></media:subTitle><media:subTitle type="text/vtt" lang="en-US" url="https://prodamdnewsencoding.akamaized.net/NBC_News_Digital/nbcnews/captions/2026/05/1777984306135_tdy_news_8a_jarrett_lively_baldoni_settlement_260505.vtt"></media:subTitle></media:content><media:thumbnail url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/mpx/2704722219/2026_05/1777984306135_tdy_news_8a_jarrett_lively_baldoni_settlement_260505_S3_1920x1080-te6gza.jpg"></media:thumbnail><pubDate>Tue, 05 May 2026 12:31:52 GMT</pubDate><title>Blake Lively and Justin Baldoni Settle ‘It Ends With Us’ Legal Battle</title><updateDate>Tue, 05 May 2026 13:18:53 GMT</updateDate></item><item><dateTimeWritten>Tue, 05 May 2026 13:36:36 GMT</dateTimeWritten><description>Nearly 150 passengers, including 17 Americans, are trapped on a cruise ship off the coast of West Africa after seven possible cases of hantavirus have now been identified aboard, according to the World Health Organization. The suspected outbreak has killed at least three people and two other patients onboard the ship are being prepared for evacuation. NBC’s Camila Bernal reports for TODAY.</description><expires>2056-05-05T11:56:54.000+0000</expires><guid isPermaLink="false">tdy_news_7a_bernal_hantavirus_cruise_260505</guid><link>https://www.today.com/video/man-makes-emotional-plea-from-hantavirus-cruise-ship-262747205579</link><media:content url="https://prodamdnewsencoding.akamaized.net/NBC_News_Digital/tdy_news_7a_bernal_hantavirus_cruise_260505/1/abs/index.m3u8" medium="video"><media:credit></media:credit><med